The paper discusses the normalization of occurrence and co-occurrence matrices in bibliometrics, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The use of similarity measures such as cosine and Pearson correlation is also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DB). The paper also mentions the use of multidimensional scaling and cluster dendograms, which are techniques commonly used in information visualization (cs.SI).
